A woman died and a man sustained burn wounds in a fire in Bellville on Saturday morning. The City's Fire and Rescue Service received an emergency call at 7.40am in connection with regards an informal structure ablaze just off the Tienie Meyer Bypass. Fire and Rescue spokesperson Jermaine Carelse said that Bellville's fire crew was quickly on scene and found a man with third degree burn wounds and the body of a woman in the structure. The male was treated and thereafter transported to Tygerberg Hospital. The fire was extinguished just after 8am. “The shelter was situated at the Caltex garage, Cross Street and would be located near Landros Street,” he said. The identities of the individuals is unknown. Weekend Argus